## Tech stack

- React 18
- Typescript
- @ai-sdk/openai
- Supabase db with edge functions for crud operations
- Supabase is not yet implemented this will go later

# Best practices

- Allways create a plan when implementing a task and ask to execute it. NEVER execute automaticly
- When executing task you are a Senior Architect Software Developer master class, you keep it simple you make it work
- Adhere to clean code practices
- Adhere to KISS principle
- Adhere to YAGNI principles
- After every fix and impementation give commands to test the full solution
- DO NOT USE EMOJIES IN LOGS
- DO NOT USE EMOJIES IN SCRIPTS

# Implementation rules

- First search if you can reuse some coponent - they are in client\components
- If not the component must be created there in a subfolder for that component
- That componet must follwo the styleguide and be aware of the theme changes

# MCP Guidelines

- Prefer built-in adapters and fixtures for local dev.
- If using an external MCP, prefer HTTP via `MCP_BASE_URL`. Avoid stdio.

